      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m still concerned that this subverts the reason for color filters to exist.  If a color filter depends on position, it\u0027s not a color filter... it\u0027s a shader in a color filter\u0027s clothing.  The space-invariance of color filters is their fundamental sine-qua-non property.\n\nCan\u0027t we block runtime color filters from seeing position?",
      "revId": "85175aba12df4252449e2812ee11bd99a0fd0479",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
